article.headline: Utah Valley St. 77, W. Illinois 75
article.story: MACOMB, Ill. (AP) -- Ryan Toolson led four Utah Valley State players in double digits Saturday with 16 points as the Wolverines beat Western Illinois 77-75. Toolson was 5-of-9 from the field, including 4-of-5 from 3-point range. Brett Ravenberg and David Heck both had 14 points and Chris Bailey chipped in 11 for Utah Valley State (4-1), which led 37-28 at halftime. The Leathernecks (2-3) were led by Sammy Hunter who had 21 points and three rebounds. David Jackson added 19 points and Mahamoud Diakite had 11.
